oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: Portrait paintings; Men; Politicians; Legislators; Military personnel; Military officers; Generals; Uniforms
Winchester, James, 1752-1826
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Fought in Revolutionary War. Moved to TN, 1785. Elected Speaker of the Senate and brigadier general, commandant of the Mero District, 1796. Developed land that would become Memphis, 1820. General during War of 1812.
